# Unmute Labs — Project Rules for Cursor

## Project Overview
Unmute Labs is a team engagement platform that delivers structured, game-based protocols to build trust and collaboration in workplace teams. The platform has two parts in this monorepo:
- `/` — Static marketing site (index.html, images/)
- `/app-platform/` — Next.js 14 application (the product)

All app development happens inside `/app-platform/`. Do not modify files outside this folder unless explicitly asked.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework:** Next.js 14+ (App Router, NOT Pages Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode, no `any` types)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- **Real-time:** Supabase Realtime (WebSocket channels)
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (Google + Microsoft SSO providers)
- **Animation:** Framer Motion (declarative, subtle transitions only)
- **Hosting:** Vercel
- **Package manager:** npm

## Design System — NEVER HARDCODE VALUES

### Colors (use Tailwind config tokens)
All colors must be referenced via Tailwind classes using these token names. NEVER use raw hex values in components.

```
unmute-navy: #1B3A5C        — Headlines, icon base, CTAs on light backgrounds
deep-navy: #0F2440          — Dark backgrounds, footer, high-contrast contexts
steel-blue: #4A6080         — Secondary text on dark backgrounds
signal-amber: #F5A623       — PRIMARY accent. CTA buttons on dark, highlights, key moments
sunrise-gold: #FFCC33       — Hover states, gradient partner to amber, success states
warm-white: #FAF8F5         — Primary background (use instead of pure white)
slate: #6B7B8D              — Body text alternative, captions, metadata
charcoal: #2D3436           — Primary body text
cloud-grey: #E8ECEF         — Dividers, borders, card backgrounds, inactive states
signal-red: #E85D4A         — Error/alert only. Never decorative.
```

### Color Ratio: 60/30/10
- 60% warm-white / cloud-grey (background, breathing room)
- 30% unmute-navy / charcoal (structure, text, authority)
- 10% signal-amber / sunrise-gold (accent, energy, CTAs)
Amber should feel like a "flash of gold" — not a flood.

### Typography (use Tailwind config tokens)
All font families must be referenced via Tailwind classes. NEVER hardcode font-family strings in components.

```
font-display: 'Outfit', sans-serif       — Headlines, H1, H2, buttons
font-mono: 'DM Mono', monospace          — Protocol labels, data, code, DM Mono Light for LABS wordmark
font-body: 'Inter', sans-serif           — Body text, UI elements, long-form
```

### Type Scale
- Display/H1: Outfit Bold, 40-48px
- H2: Outfit SemiBold, 28-32px
- H3/Subhead: Outfit Medium, 20-24px
- H4/Label: DM Mono Regular, CAPS, wide tracking, 14-16px
- Body: Inter Regular, 16-18px
- Caption: Inter Regular, 12-14px
- Data/Code: DM Mono Light, 14px

### Spacing
Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently. Prefer generous padding — the UI should breathe. Cards get p-6 or p-7 minimum. Sections get py-12 minimum.

### Border Radius
Use rounded-lg (8px) for cards and containers. Use rounded-md (6px) for buttons and inputs. Use rounded-full for avatars and badges.

### Shadows
Subtle only. Use shadow-sm as default for cards. On hover, transition to shadow-md. Never use shadow-lg or shadow-xl.

## Animation Philosophy — "A well-run workshop in a beautiful room"
- Motion communicates state changes, NEVER decorates
- Use Framer Motion for React components
- Allowed: fade, slide (translateY 4-8px), scale (0.97-1.0), opacity transitions
- FORBIDDEN: bounce, spring overshoot, confetti, shake, pulse (except for live indicators), any animation that could be described as "game show energy"
- Timing: 200-400ms for micro-interactions, 400-600ms for phase transitions
- Easing: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) for most transitions
- Stagger children by 100-150ms for list reveals

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
- Primary (amber): signal-amber background, deep-navy text. Hover: sunrise-gold. Reserved for THE one action.
- Secondary (navy): unmute-navy background, white text.
- Ghost: transparent with cloud-grey border. Hover: cloud-grey background.
- Disabled: opacity-40, cursor-not-allowed.
- Submit flow: grey (disabled) → steel-blue (active) → signal-amber (confirmed)

### Cards
- warm-white background, cloud-grey border (1px), rounded-lg
- On hover: translateY(-2px), shadow transition
- Generous internal padding (p-6 minimum)

### Protocol Labels
- DM Mono, uppercase, wide letter-spacing (tracking-widest), 10-11px
- Color: steel-blue or signal-amber depending on context

### Timers
- Time-timer style: circular arc that diminishes clockwise
- Navy fill on warm-white background
- NO numeric countdown display
- Visual metaphor: Time Timer (physical red-disc classroom timer)

### Session Progress Bar
- Thin horizontal bar (3-4px) at top of screen
- Navy fill on cloud-grey track
- No numeric labels
- Environmental — always visible, never competing for attention

## Data Architecture
- **Person** = real human (email-based identity, persists across teams)
- **Participant** = Person's membership on a specific Team (nullable person_id for guests)
- **Team** = group with one Lead and N Members, has require_auth toggle
- **Season** = 10-week engagement cycle
- **Protocol** = game/activity template
- **Session** = one instance of a Protocol being played
- **SessionState** = real-time game state (state_json holds protocol-specific data)

## File Organization (inside /app-platform/)
```
/app                    — Next.js routes
/app/api                — API routes
/components             — Shared React components
/components/providers   — Context providers (SessionProvider, etc.)
/components/ui          — Reusable UI primitives (buttons, cards, timers)
/lib                    — Utilities, Supabase client, types
/lib/supabase           — Supabase client setup
/lib/types              — TypeScript interfaces
/lib/protocols          — Protocol registry and individual protocol modules
/lib/protocols/[slug]/  — Each protocol: index.ts, component, engine, types, components/
/hooks                  — Custom React hooks
/public                 — Static assets
/scripts                — Seed scripts, utilities
/supabase/migrations    — SQL migration files
```

## Code Style
- Use named exports (not default) for utilities and hooks
- Use default exports for page components and protocol main components
- Prefer `const` arrow functions for components
- Always type props explicitly — no implicit `any`
- Use early returns for guard clauses
- Colocate protocol-specific code inside its module folder
- Keep components focused — if it's doing more than one thing, split it

## Key Constraints
- All state transitions in protocols go through sendAction() API — never mutate state client-side
- Timers display client-side but are server-authoritative for phase transitions
- Images in "Draw It By Ear" must NEVER be sent to Drawer clients — role-check before serving
- Join codes are 6 characters, uppercase alphanumeric
- Mobile-first for all participant-facing screens
- Desktop-optimized for admin screens only